{{Infobox film | name = Margaret Mee and the Moonflower | image = Margaret Mee and the Moonflower.jpg | caption = | alt = | director = Malu De Martino | producer = Elisa Tolomelli | writer = Malu De Martino | starring = [[Patrícia Pillar]] (Narrator) | music = Artur Barreiros | cinematography = | editing = | studio = E.H. Filmes | distributor = E.H. Filmes | released = {{Film date|2012|10|7|Rio Film Festival 2012|2013|04|26|Brazil}} | runtime = 78 minutes | country = Brazil | language = Portuguese | budget = | gross = }}
'''''Margaret Mee and the Moonflower''''' ({{lang-pt|Margaret Mee e a Flor da Lua}}) is a 2012 Brazilian [[documentary film]] directed by Malu De Martino, about the work and legacy of British botanical artist [[Margaret Mee]], who moved to Brazil in the 1950s, produced over 400 illustrations about Brazilian flora and, used her art as a tool to defend the environmentalism.<ref>http://www.adorocinema.com/filmes/filme-213510/</ref>
