The '''Orquesta Nacional de España''' (Spanish National Orchestra) is a symphonic orchestra that is based in [[Madrid]], Spain.<ref>{{cite web | author=| title=Orquesta Nacional de España | url=http://www.cami.com/?webid=339| publisher=Columbia Astists Management Inc. | date= | accessdate=24 August 2009}}</ref>
==History== Although the orchestra originated as of 1937, during the [[Spanish Civil War]],<ref>{{cite web|author= |title=Orquesta Nacional de Espana OCNE |url=http://www.askonasholt.co.uk/green/green/home.nsf/ArtistDetails/Orquesta%20Nacional%20de%20Espana%20OCNE |publisher=Askonas Holt |date= |accessdate=24 August 2009 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20081008114159/http://www.askonasholt.co.uk/green/green/home.nsf/ArtistDetails/Orquesta%20Nacional%20de%20Espana%20OCNE |archivedate=October 8, 2008 }}</ref> it was legally founded in 1940,<ref>{{cite web | author=Luis Mario Fraile | title=Orquestas en España| url=http://www.lafactoriadelritmo.com/fact2/orquest.shtml| publisher= | date= | accessdate=24 August 2009|language=es}}</ref> by the merging of Pérez Casas' ''Filarmónica'' and the ''Orquesta Sinfónica'' of [[Enrique Fernández Arbós]].
The first official concert of the newly founded orchestra was in March 1941 at the [[Theatre of María Guerrero|Teatro María Guerrero]] in Madrid conducted by eminent Portuguese conductor Pedro de Freitas Branco (1896-1963). The principal conductors of these first years of the orchestra were [[Ernesto Halffter]], José María Franco, [[Enrique Jordá]], [[Eduard Toldrà]] and [[Jesús Arámbarri]], until the designation of the first principal conductor of the orchestra, [[Bartolomé Pérez Casas]]. After his death the new principal conductor was [[Ataúlfo Argenta]], who was in the orchestra from 1945 as the keyboard instruments player.<ref>{{cite web | author=Luis Mario Fraile | title=Orquestas en España| url=http://www.lafactoriadelritmo.com/fact2/orquest.shtml| publisher= | date= | accessdate=24 August 2009|language=es}}</ref>
==Principal conductors== * [[Bartolomé Pérez Casas]] (1942&ndash;1947) * [[Ataúlfo Argenta]] (1947&ndash;1958) * [[Rafael Frühbeck de Burgos]] (1962&ndash;1978) * [[Antoni Ros-Marbà]] (1978&ndash;1981) * [[Jesús López-Cobos]] (1984&ndash;1989) * [[Aldo Ceccato]] (1991&ndash;1994) * [[Josep Pons]] (2003&ndash;2011) * [[David Afkham]] (2014&ndash;)<ref >Rubén Amón: «[http://www.elmundo.es/cultura/2015/02/16/54e1a7aee2704e36178b456d.html David Afkham: 'La cultura es nuestra identidad']», ''[[El Mundo (Spain)|El Mundo]]'', 16 February 2015</ref>
