The '''Wolf Prize in Arts''' is awarded once a year by the not-for-profit [[Wolf Foundation]] in [[Israel]]. It is one of the six [[Wolf Prize]]s established by the Foundation, and has been awarded since 1981; the others are in [[Wolf Prize in Agriculture|Agriculture]], [[Wolf Prize in Chemistry|Chemistry]], [[Wolf Prize in Mathematics|Mathematics]], [[Wolf Prize in Medicine|Medicine]] and [[Wolf Prize in Physics|Physics]], awarded since 1978. The Prize rotates annually among painting, music, architecture and sculpture.

